—repeal of the prohibition on furnishing long-term development assistance and short-term economic support (security supporting
                    assistance) to any country in a single fiscal year (Sec. 115 of the Foreign
                    Assistance Act of 1961, as amended—the FAA);

—we have been most effective to date in arguing, not against constraints per se,
                    but that particular constraints are undesirable on their own practical or policy
                    merits;
